Which is I defined it as delta
y-axis over delta x-axis.

00:40:57.810 --> 00:40:59.930
And yet, when I defined here
the marginal utilities, I

00:40:59.930 --> 00:41:01.880
flipped it.

00:41:01.880 --> 00:41:03.700
I did the marginal utility of
what's on the x-axis over the

00:41:03.700 --> 00:41:04.810
marginal utility of what's
on the y-axis.

00:41:04.810 --> 00:41:05.300
Why is that?

00:41:05.300 --> 00:41:06.430
Can anyone tell me
why that is?

00:41:06.430 --> 00:41:08.154
Why is it flipped
when defined in

00:41:08.154 --> 00:41:09.595
terms of marginal utilities?

00:41:09.595 --> 00:41:09.910
Yeah?

00:41:09.910 --> 00:41:12.518
AUDIENCE: It's a denominator.

00:41:12.518 --> 00:41:14.506
So utility over movies--

00:41:17.460 --> 00:41:20.510
PROFESSOR: Well, let me try for
slightly more, how does

00:41:20.510 --> 00:41:21.320
marginal utility relate?

00:41:21.320 --> 00:41:21.575
Yeah.

00:41:21.575 --> 00:41:28.291
AUDIENCE: Marginal utility
is delta P over

00:41:28.291 --> 00:41:30.279
P. So it gets flipped.

00:41:30.279 --> 00:41:30.780
Because of--

00:41:30.780 --> 00:41:32.140
PROFESSOR: OK.

00:41:32.140 --> 00:41:34.620
Yeah, you're giving the
same answer, which

00:41:34.620 --> 00:41:35.490
is technically right.

00:41:35.490 --> 00:41:38.470
What I was more looking for but
it's the intuitive version

00:41:38.470 --> 00:41:42.380
of that, marginal utility is a
negative function of quantity.

00:41:42.380 --> 00:41:44.810
Marginal utility is a negative
function of quantity.

00:41:44.810 --> 00:41:47.700
So the fact that it's a ratio of
the quantity of pizza over

00:41:47.700 --> 00:41:50.000
the quantity of movies is the
same thing as the marginal

00:41:50.000 --> 00:41:52.340
utility of movies over the
marginal utility of pizza.

00:41:52.340 --> 00:41:54.890
Because marginal utility is a
negative function of quantity.

00:41:54.890 --> 00:41:56.300
The more quantity you
have, the lower is

00:41:56.300 --> 00:41:58.440
your marginal utility.

00:41:58.440 --> 00:42:01.060
And that's the key
to understand.

00:42:01.060 --> 00:42:05.460
So it's the slope of the
indifference curve which is

00:42:05.460 --> 00:42:07.485
the ratio of the marginal
utilities, but it's the

00:42:07.485 --> 00:42:10.700
marginal utility of
movies over pizza.

00:42:10.700 --> 00:42:14.290
Because what that's saying is
that as you get more movies,

00:42:14.290 --> 00:42:17.730
you care less about each
additional movie and ditto

00:42:17.730 --> 00:42:18.980
with pizzas.

00:42:20.870 --> 00:42:22.250
Let's just look at this for
a minute, think about it

00:42:22.250 --> 00:42:23.270
intuitively for a minute.

00:42:23.270 --> 00:42:25.590
We've seen it graphically,
we're seeing it

00:42:25.590 --> 00:42:27.510
mathematically, let's make
sure we understand it

00:42:27.510 --> 00:42:29.120
intuitively.

00:42:29.120 --> 00:42:33.630
What this is saying is that
as you get more movies--

00:42:33.630 --> 00:42:36.470
so let's relate this
to the graph.

00:42:36.470 --> 00:42:41.800
As you get more movies and less
pizza, as you move down

00:42:41.800 --> 00:42:45.160
that curve, more movies, less
pizza, what's happening?

00:42:45.160 --> 00:42:46.930
What's happening to the marginal
utility of movies as

00:42:46.930 --> 00:42:48.650
you move down that curve?

00:42:48.650 --> 00:42:50.190
What direction is it heading?

00:42:50.190 --> 00:42:51.500
AUDIENCE: It's decreasing.

00:42:51.500 --> 00:42:51.870
PROFESSOR: What?

00:42:51.870 --> 00:42:52.240
AUDIENCE: It's decreasing.

00:42:52.240 --> 00:42:54.270
PROFESSOR: It's decreasing.

00:42:54.270 --> 00:42:56.540
Because you're getting more
movies and marginal utility is

00:42:56.540 --> 00:42:58.260
a negative function
of quantity.

00:42:58.260 --> 00:43:02.770
Likewise, the marginal utility
of pizza is increasing because

00:43:02.770 --> 00:43:05.850
you're getting less
pizza so you care

00:43:05.850 --> 00:43:07.720
about each pizza more.

00:43:07.720 --> 00:43:10.900
And that's why the marginal
rate of substitution

00:43:10.900 --> 00:43:12.150
diminishes.

00:43:13.940 --> 00:43:16.470
That's why it diminishes because
as you move down that

00:43:16.470 --> 00:43:19.830
curve, the numerator is falling,
the denominator is

00:43:19.830 --> 00:43:20.690
increasing.

00:43:20.690 --> 00:43:23.220
And that's why we have
everywhere diminishing

00:43:23.220 --> 00:43:24.470
marginal rates of
substitution.

00:43:27.790 --> 00:43:35.140
So another way to think about
this is imagine for a moment

00:43:35.140 --> 00:43:38.150
what life would be like if we
didn't have diminishing

00:43:38.150 --> 00:43:39.990
marginal rates of
substitution.

00:43:39.990 --> 00:43:42.460
And once again I'm going to try,
once again Jessica, next

00:43:42.460 --> 00:43:43.700
year we'll let you
make this pretty.

00:43:43.700 --> 00:43:46.450
But I'm going to try to
draw it crudely here.

00:43:46.450 --> 00:43:48.990
Let's do pizzas and
movies again.

00:43:52.570 --> 00:43:53.980
Let's do pizzas and
