00:45:27.210 --> 00:45:29.740
see it a second time, why would
you possibly give up two

00:45:29.740 --> 00:45:30.870
pizzas to see it a third time?

00:45:30.870 --> 00:45:32.510
You wouldn't.

00:45:32.510 --> 00:45:33.650
It doesn't make sense.

00:45:33.650 --> 00:45:36.930
And that's why marginal rate
of substitution has to be

00:45:36.930 --> 00:45:39.520
everywhere decreasing, it
can't be increasing.

00:45:39.520 --> 00:45:39.795
Yeah?

